The paper deals with action recognition using CNNs and handcrafted representations, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves end-to-end training of networks, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Bag-of-Words and Fisher Vectors for encoding low-level video descriptors is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also involves the use of optical flow features, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
